parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the anti-theft system can cause the vehicle to not start, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially putting them and their passengers at risk in extreme weather conditions.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
the security system warning light illuminates
the vehicle locks and unlocks randomly
the horn honks weakly
and the vehicle shuts off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Conditioning and Heating System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning and heating system can cause overheating, burning odors, and electrical fires, potentially putting the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: The air conditioning and heating system shut off independently
there is a burning odor emitting from the AC vents
the blower motor resistor and wiring harness melt or burn
and the AC and heating system fail to work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various electrical components to malfunction, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The windshield wipers fail to work
the trailer brakes and lights fail to function
and the electrical wiring harness melts or burns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause injuries, distractions, and accidents, potentially leading to fatalities.
symptoms: The airbags deploy without any impact or collision
often while driving at low speeds
and may cause injuries
noise
and damage to the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty rollover sensor can cause the airbags to deploy unnecessarily, leading to injuries and accidents, or fail to deploy in the event of a real rollover, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard is illuminated
and the vehicle may have a history of unintended airbag deployments.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical fault in the Supplemental Restraint System (SRS) can cause the airbags to deploy unnecessarily, leading to injuries and accidents, or fail to deploy in the event of a real crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard is illuminated
and the vehicle may have a history of unintended airbag deployments.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust system can cause the exhaust bolts to break or the manifold to crack, leading to exhaust fumes leaking into the cabin, which can cause dizziness, nausea, and even loss of consciousness.
symptoms: Exhaust fumes leaking into the cabin
abnormal sounds or smells from the exhaust system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine knocking or misfire can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Abnormal knocking or misfiring sounds from the engine
check engine warning light illuminated
engine stalling or loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator can cause coolant to leak, leading to overheating, engine damage, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Coolant leaking from the radiator
temperature gauge displaying high temperatures
radiator cracking or fracturing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the balancer bolt can cause the engine to misfire, stall, or lose power, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine misfiring or stalling
audible whining noise from the engine
oil loss.
